2.3 Update The Browser Tab label
Lesson
When working with multiple ServiceNow instances—such as Development (DEV), Test, User Acceptance Testing (UAT), and Production (PROD)—it's critical to know which environment you're currently using. System Properties in ServiceNow provide configuration options that control system behavior without requiring code. One essential configuration is the Browser tab title, which adds a visual identifier to your browser tab and throughout the interface, helping prevent costly mistakes like making changes in the wrong environment.

Scenario
You are the ServiceNow System Administrator for Cloud Dimensions. Your organization has multiple ServiceNow instances for different purposes. You're currently working in the Development (DEV) instance where administrators and developers configure and build applications. To avoid confusion and ensure you always know which instance you're using, you need to configure the browser tab title to display "CD DEV" (Cloud Dimensions Development). This identifier will appear in your browser tab and in contextual elements throughout the platform.

Task Objectives
1. Navigate to the Basic Configuration system properties.

2. Configure the Browser tab title property to display "CD DEV".

3. Save the configuration and verify the label appears in your browser tab.

4. Identify the Contextual app pill and confirm the DEV label is visible.

5. Add the System Properties page as a favorite for quick future access.




5. Publish the theme and set it as the default for your instance and verify the theme is successfully applied across the instance.

6. Unpublish the theme (to avoid accessibility issues in future tasks).
